  <h1>Indoor Plant Fertilizing Calendar – Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
  <h2>How often should I fertilize my indoor plants?</h2>
  <p>Most plants do best when fertilized every 4–6 weeks during their active growing seasons (spring and summer).</p>

  <h2>Do indoor plants need fertilizer in winter?</h2>
  <p>Typically no — plants grow slowly or go dormant and don’t require feeding.</p>

  <h2>What fertilizer should I use?</h2>
  <p>A liquid, balanced houseplant fertilizer is ideal. Look for labels like 10-10-10 or 20-20-20.</p>
